Bluetongue, Austria
--------------------
Information received on (and dated) 7 Nov 2008 from Mr Ulrich Herzog,
magister, Radetzkystrasse 2, Bundesministerium fur Gesundheit und Frauen,
Vienne, Austria

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 31 Oct 2008
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 7 Nov 2008
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Nov 2008
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus Serotype 8
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Wibling, Scharding, Oberosterreich
Date of start of the outbreak: 31 Oct 2008
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 36 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: small farm (36 free-range cattle, 14 pigs, 3 horses, 9
goats)

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: in the frame of routine screening on infectious
bovine rhinotracheitis (IBR) and infectious pustular vulvovaginitis (IPV),
samples of ruminants are investigated for BTV as well. The affected animal
is clinically healthy.

Control measures
Measures applied
- control of arthropods
- movement control inside the country
- screening
- zoning
- dipping/spraying
- no vaccination
- no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Austrian Agency for Health and Food Safety (AGES)
(National laboratory)
Tests and results
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / competitive ELISA (c-ELISA) / 7 Nov 2008 / positive
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 7 Nov 2008 / positive
Cattle / real-time PCR / 7 Nov 2008 / positive
Cattle / real-time reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction
(RRT-PCR) / 7 Nov 2008 / positive
Cattle / serotyping / 7 Nov 2008 / positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[The affected farm is very close to the German border, but no cases of
bluetongue have reportedly been detected in this part of south eastern
Germany (Bavaria). It would be helpful to note the detailed history of the
single positive, non-clinically affected cow, excluding possible past
importation. - Mod.AS]

